Suzano Signs Equipment Contracts for Northeastern Brazil Paper, Pulp Plant

-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 
2011-04-18T16:45:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/suzano-signs-equipment-contracts-for-brazil-paper-and-pulp-plant.html
Suzano Papel e Celulose SA (SUZB5) , the
Brazilian pulp and paper company, will buy power generation
equipment worth as much as $50 million from Siemens AG for a
factory it’s planning in the north eastern state of Maranhao.  Two generators will provide electricity to run the
facility’s operations, Suzano said in a filing today. About 100
megawatts of capacity will sell to the grid, according to the
statement.  The factory will begin production in April 2013, Salvador-
based Suzano  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 